<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/1939238-what-do-chickens-symbolize">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[What do chickens symbolize? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1939238'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F33363.Mama_Day">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1939238-what-do-chickens-symbolize">9 months ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1939238-what-do-chickens-symbolize">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/57812461-beanie"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1618935990i/57812461._UX100_CR0,38,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/57812461-beanie">Beanie</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    The chickens represent a few things. The chickens tell Mama Day when something is coming, like watch-dogs. Mama Day takes care of them and trusts them<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    The chickens represent a few things. The chickens tell Mama Day when something is coming, like watch-dogs. Mama Day takes care of them and trusts them so they watch for her. Chickens are shown in different parts of the book like when Mama Day tells Carmen Rae to get one for food. The chickens are also George's fear and they are an obstacle for him to overcome. Mama Day uses them to challenge George so he can come back to Mama Day as a believer, but he ends up dying since he took his own way out. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
