        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46330406-maria?shelf=books-to-read-again">books-to-read-again</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46330406-maria?shelf=willmakemethinkforever">willmakemethinkforever</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/46330406-maria?shelf=my-feminist-education">my-feminist-education</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2975051308" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10116317332864719491">This book is like someone you didn&apos;t like at first who then becomes your best friend and then you lose the friendship and cry. <br/>I want to coin the term Reader&apos;s Grief, just for this book. <br/>I wish I could go to the world these pages have created over and over. The characters are so lifelike, they spring out of the pages, they grip you tight, they will haunt my thoughts and dreams. I didn&apos;t know what I was getting myself into, I didn&apos;t know I would dive so deep that I would lose my breath in this lo</span>
  <span id="freeText10116317332864719491" style="display:none">This book is like someone you didn't like at first who then becomes your best friend and then you lose the friendship and cry. <br />I want to coin the term Reader's Grief, just for this book. <br />I wish I could go to the world these pages have created over and over. The characters are so lifelike, they spring out of the pages, they grip you tight, they will haunt my thoughts and dreams. I didn't know what I was getting myself into, I didn't know I would dive so deep that I would lose my breath in this love story that. <br />Maybe all I am left with is the feeling of having touched ancient wisdom and hoping for a love this profound.<br /><br />p.49<br />Knowing that as long as the old survived, you can keep changing as much as you want without the nightmare of waking up to a total stranger.<br /><br />p.119<br />How will I handle all this space he's creating without him to fill it?<br /><br />p.119<br />It was horrible feeling that I needed you more than I was needed.<br /><br />p.121<br />Here was a relationship I needed to turn into a catastrophe, out of fear of losing a perfect one. <br /><br />p.162<br />When you raise s god instead of a child, you're bound to be serving him for the rest of your days.<br /><br />p.226<br />I was that sure about us; we could defy history. Obviously, I was not the first young man to stand on that verandah and feel that way.<br /><br />p.230<br />Just like that chicken coop, everything got four sides: his side, her side, an outside, and an inside.<br /><br />p.234<br />No, true stupidity is genetic. Your ignorance is a deliberate choice.<br /><br />p 240<br />The point is that if your care about someone enough, you give 'em a chance to take back the things they may have said in anger. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10116317332864719491" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
